The paper discusses data management problems related to thresholded similarity searches, which are commonly studied in the fields of databases (cs.DB), data structures (cs.DS), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new principle called the pigeonring principle to solve these problems, which can be applied to various sub-fields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DB, cs.DS, cs.IR, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
